    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Oligopeptide-249 r-Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1) is a single chain recombinant peptide produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the genes from Oligopeptide-249 and r-Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1. The fusion peptide contains 459 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence from the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
